8511     // the scalar loop's latch terminator because: (a) it is all compiler
8512     // generated, (b) these instructions are always executed after evaluating
8513     // the latch conditional branch, and (c) other passes may add new
8514     // predecessors which terminate on this line. This is the easiest way to
8515     // ensure we don't accidentally cause an extra step back into the loop while
8516     // debugging.
8517     DebugLoc ExitDL = OrigLoop->getLoopLatch()->getTerminator()->getDebugLoc();
